<statement>
<p>What is the solution to <m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{3}={5}{x}+{15}</m>? <input type="text" style="width:4.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/> Â  </p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>3</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{3}={5}{x}+{15}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}+{3}-{15}={5}{x}+{15}-{15}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}-{12}={5}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{x}-{12}-{9}{x}={5}{x}-{9}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{12}=-{4}{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{12}}{{-{{4}}}}=\frac{{-{4}{x}}}{{-{{4}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}={x}</m>.</p>

</solution>
